cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI

The paper deals with offline handwriting recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves leveraging the content type within an LSTM-based architecture, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) subfields such as cs.CL and cs.LG. The authors also mention the use of synthetic data generation, which is a common technique in ML and AI (cs.AI). Finally, the dataset used in the experiments is related to accident reports, which could potentially fall under information retrieval (IR) (cs.IR).
